{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "CinematicScene",
  "description": "Physical-camera 3D scene with true depth of field, contact-shadow AO, and velocity-directed motion blur (docs/CINEMATIC_POST_DESIGN.md D6). A faceted mesh under one key light, shot through node.camera_lens (the one lens node.render_scene's exposure, the dof group's circle-of-confusion, AND node.motion_blur's shutter angle all read), an 'ao' node group (ssao_gtao -> bilateral_blur denoise -> mix(Multiply) contact-occlusion arm), a 'dof' node group (coc_from_depth -> coc_dilate -> bokeh_gather occlusion-aware disc gather, dilate fixing BUG-137's hard cutoff at depth discontinuities), and a motion_blur tail reading render_scene's velocity output. The ao/dof groups (docs/NODE_GROUPS_DESIGN.md) are pure presentation: they flatten to the same atom graph at load time, each atom stays independently wireable elsewhere. Grown incrementally across CINEMATIC_POST's phases: P1 shipped the DoF chain; P2 added the SSAO arm; P3 added the motion-blur tail; BUG-137 added the coc_dilate stage; P4 swapped variable_blur(H)+variable_blur(V) for one node.bokeh_gather; grouped into 'ao'/'dof' boxes for readability post-P4.",
